CHOLERA, IMPORTED - JAPAN (02)
******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Cholera, imported - Japan 980828234714
Date: Sat, 29 Aug 1998 10:48:13 -0700
From: Stephen A. Berger, M.D. <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on cholera in Japan were abstracted from the
GIDEON software program:
1,114 cases were reported during 1962 to 1993 (including 792 imported).
110 cases were reported during an outbreak in Arida City in 1977 (traced to
a case imported from the Philippines).
70 cases in Ikenohata (Tokyo) in 1978 were acquired from imported
Indonesian lobsters. 90 cases were reported during an outbreak in Nagoya in
1989.
An outbreak of 21 cases (1 fatal) in Tokyo during 1991 was traced to
imported Korean clams.
Recent outbreaks:
Year Cases Imported Comments
1992 52 49
1993 102 99 No fatalities
1994 114 90 0 fatal; 6 autochthonous (Okinawa)
1995 377 341 1 fatal; 296 imported from Indonesia
1996 62 49 0 fatal
1997 101 65 1 fatal
1998 14 14 0 fatal; data for January to June, 1998

_V. cholerae_ O139 (3 cases) was first reported in 1993. Eight additional
cases were reported in 1994 and 1 in 1997.
--
Dr. Steve Berger
e-mail: mberger@post.tau.ac.il
